In January, the average temperature in Saihanba National Forest Park falls to minus 15 degrees Celsius. The Tuligen, a narrow river, serves as part of the boundary between north China's Hebei Province and Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region and is the source of the Luanhe River, the second-longest river in north China. About 'Journeys in Nature': Hebei series Hebei Province in north China hosts the largest forest park in northern China, Saihanba National Forest Park, and the country's largest expanse of coastal sand dunes, the Golden Coast National Nature Reserve. Here, you will find unique landforms and a rich variety of plants and animals. For more: Hebei series | Episode 1: Beautiful Highland (Cover image via a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)